title: One-way ANOVA
text: First, calculate the sum of square errors and the mean square errors. Make sure you have use $$3$$ collumns to record your data onto your graphing calculator.

title: One-way ANOVA
text: After inputting your data onto your graphing table, use the ANOVA function on the calculator. ANOVA function typically requires that you specify which collumns to use (e.g. $$3$$ collumns L1,L2, and L3 contain data. Input ANOVA(L1,L2,L3))

title: One-way ANOVA
text: After performing the ANOVA test function, $$SS_{within}$$ can usually be found under the "Error" section, where a value $$SS=441$$ is shown.
